HEADWORD: Sphygmogram
<hw>Sphyg"mo*gram</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<?/<?/<?/<?/ pulse + <ets>-gram</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>A tracing, called a pulse tracing, consisting of a series of curves
corresponding with the beats of the heart, obtained by the application
of the sphygmograph.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

